snippet.textDisplay:
In the grand scheme of things, I personally don't care who wins, they all deserve it, especially when you look at the scale of everyone's achievement. On so many levels it's showcased a lot about humans;

If you don't ask, you don't get.

Regardless of language barriers, people love to help those in need, without expecting something in return.

A little risk can heed great reward.

It's often the little things in life that make the biggest difference.

Please and thank you go a damned long way.

Good luck to the finalists, and congrats to Simon and then sponsors for a fantastic short series.
